          <li>
            <h4>How do we work?</h4>
            <p>Just fill out our briefing form. This will only take about 5 minutes. Based on that basic information, we will create a design sample in a way we feel best suits your company's focus and vision. You need not waste anymore time on meetings.</p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h4>Why should I use this service?</h4>
            <p>Technically oriented Internet companies often do not possess a feeling for design and usability while print-design oriented companies do not have the know-how regarding specific requirements and various technical possibilities. Fortunately, we have the advantages of both.</p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h4>What do I do if I don't like the design?</h4>
            <p>Your current designer can continue working with our original files. You are free to use only parts of our design or not use it at all.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>How much does it cost?</h4>
            <p>We charge 900 USD per design sample. For 200 USD more you get a 3 day express service. Customer from Switzerland add 7.6% VAT.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>How do I pay?</h4>
            <p>After you have completed our briefing form you will receive an invoice by email. As soon as the money has been received, we will start working for you.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>How long does it take?</h4>
            <p>After your payment has arrived on our bank account, it takes about 14 days. If you choose our "Express service" it takes 3 days.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>Who does the design?</h4>
            <p>All designs are done by Oliver Schmid. An experienced designer who worked for two of the largest internet companies in Switzerland for seven years before starting the design studio Webgarten GmbH in Widen near Zurich.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>What do I get?</h4>
            <p>You get a design sample as a graphic document. It usually contains a front and second page. In addition, we will include the original workfiles. Naturally, you are free to use these any way you choose.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>How much time does it take you to do a design sample?</h4>
